---
// Byline + mandatory disclosure for every blog post. Keep this exact framing:
// Winnie is disclosed as a virtual/AI host, not a real person. We do NOT claim
// hands-on product testing anywhere on this site — Winnie showcases picks the
// real editorial team compiled from verified buyer reviews, she doesn't test
// or own the products herself (see about.astro "Meet Winnie" section +
// Brand-Guide.md §2).
---
<div class="winnie-byline">
  <img src="/winnie/avatar.jpg" alt="Winnie Hollowell" width="76" height="76" />
  <div>
    <p class="name">Winnie Hollowell <span class="role">— Nest &amp; Nook's virtual host</span></p>
    <p class="disclosure-line">Winnie is a virtual, AI-generated spokesperson, not a real person. She's showcasing picks here, not testing them herself — the actual review research behind every pick is done by our real editorial team. <a href="/about/#meet-winnie">What does that mean?</a></p>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .winnie-byline {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
  }
  .winnie-byline img {
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--gold);
    flex: none;
  }
  .winnie-byline .name {
    margin: 0 0 0.2rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .winnie-byline .role {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .winnie-byline .disclosure-line {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 52ch;
  }
  .winnie-byline .disclosure-line a { color: var(--ink-soft); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
